---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<MainLayout title="SRP Portfolio - frontpage">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <div id="cursor"></div>
  <section id="hero" class="relative container mx-auto text-center py-20">
    <!-- Content of Hero Section (kept on top with z-index) -->
    <div class="relative z-10">
      <h1 id="hero-title" class="font-bold text-gray-200 tracking-wider pt-52">Hey there!</h1>
      <h2 id="hero-subtitle" class="font-medium text-gray-300 mt-4 mb-12 tracking-widest">Welcome to my portfolio</h2>
      <p id="hero-text" class="text-gray-300 mt-6 leading-7 md:max-w-3xl max-w-md mx-auto">
        Hi! <br class="md:hidden block" /> I'm Sara Ringkow Petersen, an aspiring multimedia-designer with a strong passion for creating engaging and accessible
        digital experiences. Further down the page, you can read a bit about who I am, look through some of my projects&mdash; highlighted or not &mdash;or
        simply reach out if you have any questions or just want to say hi. <br /><br />Use the navigation menu to get started, or click the "View
        projects"-button below.
      </p>
      <div id="hero-button" class="button-container">
        <a
          href="#projects"
          class="relative z-10 text-gray-300 bg-site-red font-bold rounded-lg text-sm px-6 py-3 inline-flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden group mt-8 transition duration-300 uppercase"
        >
          <span class="button-text text-sm relative z-10 w-full text-center uppercase">View projects</span>
          <span class="absolute inset-0 bg-red-600 transition-transform duration-500 ease-in-out translate-x-full group-hover:translate-x-0"></span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About Section -->
  <section id="about" class="container mx-auto pt-52 pb-16 px-4">
    <div class="bg-gray-700 bg-opacity-80 p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center">
      <div class="lg:w-1/2 lg:pr-8">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-200">About me</h3>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-300 leading-7">
          As a multimedia-designer, I <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">specialise</span> in UX and web design, with a strong
          focus on <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">accessibility</span> and inclusive design. I have a deep understanding
          of the meaning of design, its impact on usability, and the overall importance of creating visually engaging and user-friendly interfaces. As
          someone who's <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">late-diagnosed</span>
          with autism, I know what it's like to be a person who's not fully capable of certain things and have limited understanding of the world around
          them. This has led me to my <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">main goal</span>&mdash; to create digital
          experiences that are accessible and inclusive for all users, regardless of their disabilities.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-300 leading-7">
          <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">Creativity</span> is at the heart of everything I do, driving me to explore the
          world of design with enthusiasm and curiosity. Each project
          <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">presents a chance</span> to transform ideas into meaningful experiences. I thrive
          on the excitement of
          <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">experimenting with new techniques</span> and discovering innovative ways to bring
          concepts to life. As I journey through this ever-evolving field, I look forward to <span
            class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">embracing new challenges</span
          > and forging connections that <span class="highlight-text text-site-red font-bold text-lg">inspire</span> growth and creativity. The future
          holds endless possibilities, and I'm eager to see where this path will lead me.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex justify-center lg:w-1/2 mt-8 lg:mt-0">
        <img src="images/pfp.webp" alt="About Me Image" class="w-[350px] h-[350px] rounded-full shadow-md object-cover" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Projects Section -->
  <div id="projects" class="pt-52">
    <section id="project-section" class="container mx-auto px-4 bg-gray-800 bg-opacity-70 rounded-lg shadow-lg mt-8">
      <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold max-w-4xl mx-auto text-gray-100 text-left pt-12 pb-4">Highlighted projects</h3>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-300 text-left leading-7 max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-[2rem]">
        I have worked on a lot of different projects in the past, each different in its own way. However, some of them are not as important as others.
        When taking this sort of course, you're bound to have both favorite and least favorite projects. Because you can't always decide what kind of
        project you have to do. I've decided to highlight some of the projects that I'm most proud of.
      </p>

